"""
Faithful reproduction of MoDA (Mixture-of-Depth Attention) for the LeWM
latent dynamics predictor.

Uses the original MoDA Triton kernel ``parallel_moda`` for depth-augmented
causal attention.  Each predictor layer stores its K/V; deeper layers
retrieve *all* previous layers' K/V at the **same sequence position** and
compete them against temporal K/V inside a single unified softmax — exactly
as defined in the MoDA paper.

Depth cache layout (matches MoDA convention):
  cached_k : [B, T * L, H, D]   (L = number of cached layers)
  cached_v : [B, T * L, H, D]

When ``use_moda=False`` the predictor is architecturally identical to the
original LeWM ``ARPredictor`` (pure causal sequence attention, no depth
memory).  This serves as the control condition.
"""

